dispersion of its production facilities, the company uses numerous sources for
the wide variety of raw materials needed for its operations. the company has not
been adversely affected by inability to obtain raw materials.
the company owns,
or holds licenses to use, numerous patents. new patents are continuously being
obtained through the company's research and development activities as existing
patents expire. patented inventions are used both within the company and
licensed to others, but no operating segment is substantially dependent on any
single patent or group of related patents.
