billion, of which $26.8 billion was restricted.
at december 31, 2000 and 1999, the aggregate statutory capital and surplus of
the insurance businesses totaled $16.2 billion and $14.5 billion, respectively.
accounting practices prescribed by statutory authorities are used in preparing
statutory statements.
